Measuring inequalities: RII and SII - anemia

Pearl Ante-Testard

2024-12-16

source(here::here("R", "0-config.R"))
# Load the data
df_analysis_anemia <- readRDS(file = here::here("data", "1-final", "df_analysis_iwi.rds")) %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(study = sub("s[0-9]*_", "", study.x)) %>%
  select(study, pid, region, cluster, arms_maternal, iwi, b2_anemia_el) %>% 
  dplyr::filter(!is.na(iwi)) %>%
  dplyr::filter(!is.na(arms_maternal)) %>%
  dplyr::filter(!is.na(b2_anemia_el)) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(
    arms_maternal = factor(arms_maternal, levels = c(0, 1), labels = c("Control", "SQ-LNS")),
    iwi = as.numeric(iwi),
    cluster = factor(cluster),
    b2_anemia_el = factor(b2_anemia_el),
    iwi_decile = ntile(iwi, 10)
  )

# Calculate the ECDF for iwi_decile
ecdf_iwi_decile <- ecdf(df_analysis_anemia$iwi_decile)

# Apply the ECDF to get the relative rank
df_analysis_anemia <- df_analysis_anemia %>%
  mutate(iwi_relative_rank = ecdf_iwi_decile(iwi_decile))

# Print the data frame with the new relative rank column
print(df_analysis_anemia)

RII and SII estimates from the glm model

Here, used iwi in the model.

RII > 1 or SII > 0: b2_anemia_el is higher among the poor than the rich; RII = 1 or SII = 0: no inequality

ineq <- df_analysis_anemia %>%
  split(.$study) %>%
  map_dfr(function(df_analysis_anemia) {
    study_name <- unique(df_analysis_anemia$study)
    results <- list()
    
    if (study_name %in% c("DOSE", "GHANA", "HAITI", "DYADG", "DYADM")) {
      # Control group
      df_control <- df_analysis_anemia %>% filter(arms_maternal == "Control")
      glm_c <- glm(b2_anemia_el ~ iwi_relative_rank, family = binomial(link = "log"), 
                   data = df_control)
      glm_c_robust_vcov <- vcovCL(glm_c, cluster = NULL)
      glm_c_lin_robustse <- coeftest(glm_c, vcov. = glm_c_robust_vcov)
      
      beta_glm_c <- coef(glm_c)[1] - (coef(glm_c)[1] + coef(glm_c)[2])
      RII_glm_c <- exp(beta_glm_c)
      se_b1 <- glm_c_lin_robustse[2, 2]
      RII_low <- exp(beta_glm_c - 1.96 * se_b1)
      RII_up <- exp(beta_glm_c + 1.96 * se_b1)
      
      SII_glm_c <- exp(coef(glm_c)[1]) - exp(coef(glm_c)[1] + coef(glm_c)[2])
      b <- coef(glm_c_lin_robustse)
      SII_sd <- deltamethod(~exp(x1) - exp(x1 + x2), b, glm_c_robust_vcov)
      SII_low <- SII_glm_c - 1.96 * SII_sd
      SII_up <- SII_glm_c + 1.96 * SII_sd
      
      results$control <- list(RII = RII_glm_c, RII_low = RII_low, RII_up = RII_up,
                              SII = SII_glm_c, SII_low = SII_low, SII_up = SII_up)
      
      # Intervention group
      df_interv <- df_analysis_anemia %>% filter(arms_maternal == "SQ-LNS")
      glm_i <- glm(b2_anemia_el ~ iwi_relative_rank, family = binomial(link = "log"), 
                   data = df_interv)
      glm_i_robust_vcov <- vcovCL(glm_i, cluster = NULL)
      glm_i_lin_robustse <- coeftest(glm_i, vcov. = glm_i_robust_vcov)
      
      beta_glm_i <- coef(glm_i)[1] - (coef(glm_i)[1] + coef(glm_i)[2])
      RII_glm_i <- exp(beta_glm_i)
      se_b1_i <- glm_i_lin_robustse[2, 2]
      RII_low_i <- exp(beta_glm_i - 1.96 * se_b1_i)
      RII_up_i <- exp(beta_glm_i + 1.96 * se_b1_i)
      
      SII_glm_i <- exp(coef(glm_i)[1]) - exp(coef(glm_i)[1] + coef(glm_i)[2])
      b_i <- coef(glm_i_lin_robustse)
      SII_sd_i <- deltamethod(~exp(x1) - exp(x1 + x2), b_i, glm_i_robust_vcov)
      SII_low_i <- SII_glm_i - 1.96 * SII_sd_i
      SII_up_i <- SII_glm_i + 1.96 * SII_sd_i
      
      results$intervention <- list(RII = RII_glm_i, RII_low = RII_low_i, RII_up = RII_up_i,
                                   SII = SII_glm_i, SII_low = SII_low_i, SII_up = SII_up_i)
      
    } else {
      # Control group
      df_control <- df_analysis_anemia %>% filter(arms_maternal == "Control") %>% 
        mutate(b2_anemia_el = as.numeric(b2_anemia_el) - 1)
      gee_c <- geeglm(b2_anemia_el ~ iwi_relative_rank,
               family = poisson(link="log"), id=cluster,  corstr='independence', 
               std.err = "san.se",
               data = df_control)
        #glm(b2_anemia_el ~ iwi_relative_rank, family = binomial(link = "log"), data = df_control)
      #glm_c_robust_vcov <- vcovCL(glm_c, cluster = df_control$cluster)
      #glm_c_lin_robustse <- coeftest(glm_c, vcov. = glm_c_robust_vcov)
      
      beta_gee_c <- coef(gee_c)[1] - (coef(gee_c)[1] + coef(gee_c)[2])
      RII_gee_c <- exp(beta_gee_c)
      se_b1 <- coef(summary(gee_c))[2,"Std.err"]
      RII_low <- exp(RII_gee_c - 1.96 * se_b1)
      RII_up <- exp(RII_gee_c + 1.96 * se_b1)
      
      SII_gee_c <- exp(coef(gee_c)[1]) - exp(coef(gee_c)[1] + coef(gee_c)[2])
      b <- coef(gee_c)
      v <- vcov(gee_c)
      SII_sd <- deltamethod(~exp(x1) - exp(x1 + x2), b, v)
      SII_low <- SII_gee_c - 1.96 * SII_sd
      SII_up <- SII_gee_c + 1.96 * SII_sd
      
      results$control <- list(RII = RII_gee_c, RII_low = RII_low, RII_up = RII_up,
                              SII = SII_gee_c, SII_low = SII_low, SII_up = SII_up)
      
      # Intervention group
      df_interv <- df_analysis_anemia %>% filter(arms_maternal == "SQ-LNS")%>% 
        mutate(b2_anemia_el = as.numeric(b2_anemia_el) - 1)
      gee_i <- geeglm(b2_anemia_el ~ iwi_relative_rank,
               family = poisson(link="log"), id=cluster,  corstr='independence', 
               std.err = "san.se",
               data = df_interv)
        #glm(b2_anemia_el ~ iwi_relative_rank, family = binomial(link = "log"), data = df_control)
      #glm_c_robust_vcov <- vcovCL(glm_c, cluster = df_control$cluster)
      #glm_c_lin_robustse <- coeftest(glm_c, vcov. = glm_c_robust_vcov)
      
      beta_gee_i <- coef(gee_i)[1] - (coef(gee_i)[1] + coef(gee_i)[2])
      RII_gee_i <- exp(beta_gee_i)
      se_b1 <- coef(summary(gee_i))[2,"Std.err"]
      RII_low <- exp(RII_gee_c - 1.96 * se_b1)
      RII_up <- exp(RII_gee_c + 1.96 * se_b1)
      
      SII_gee_i <- exp(coef(gee_i)[1]) - exp(coef(gee_i)[1] + coef(gee_i)[2])
      b <- coef(gee_i)
      v <- vcov(gee_i)
      SII_sd <- deltamethod(~exp(x1) - exp(x1 + x2), b, v)
      SII_low <- SII_gee_i - 1.96 * SII_sd
      SII_up <- SII_gee_i + 1.96 * SII_sd
      
      
      results$intervention <- list(RII = RII_gee_i, RII_low = RII_low, RII_up = RII_up,
                                   SII = SII_gee_i, SII_low = SII_low, SII_up = SII_up)
    }
    
    # Create a data frame with the results
    ineq_tab <- data.frame(
      study = study_name,
      RII_control = round(results$control$RII, 3),
      RII_low_control = round(results$control$RII_low, 3),
      RII_up_control = round(results$control$RII_up, 3),
      SII_control = round(results$control$SII, 3),
      SII_low_control = round(results$control$SII_low, 3),
      SII_up_control = round(results$control$SII_up, 3),
      RII_intervention = round(results$intervention$RII, 3),
      RII_low_intervention = round(results$intervention$RII_low, 3),
      RII_up_intervention = round(results$intervention$RII_up, 3),
      SII_intervention = round(results$intervention$SII, 3),
      SII_low_intervention = round(results$intervention$SII_low, 3),
      SII_up_intervention = round(results$intervention$SII_up, 3)
    )
    
    return(ineq_tab)
  })

print(ineq)
# Calculate the prevalence of b2_anemia_el by study
prevalence_values_anemia <- df_analysis_anemia %>%
  group_by(study, arms_maternal) %>%
  summarise(
    prevalence_b2_anemia_el = mean(b2_anemia_el == 1, na.rm = TRUE),
    sd_b2_anemia_el = sd(b2_anemia_el == 1, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) 
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'study'. You can override using the `.groups`
## argument.
# Calculate the overall prevalence of b2_anemia_el by study
overall_prevalence_anemia <- df_analysis_anemia %>%
  group_by(study) %>%
  summarise(
    prevalence_b2_anemia_el = mean(b2_anemia_el == 1, na.rm = TRUE),  # Calculate the prevalence
    sd_b2_anemia_el = sd(b2_anemia_el == 1, na.rm = TRUE)
  )

Meta-analysis

df_sqlns <- subset(prevalence_values_anemia, (arms_maternal %in% c("SQ-LNS"))) 
colnames(df_sqlns) <- c("study", "arms_maternal", "prevalence_b2_anemia_el_sqlns",
                        "sd_b2_anemia_el_sqlns")
df_control <- subset(prevalence_values_anemia, (arms_maternal %in% c("Control")))
colnames(df_control) <- c("study", "arms_maternal", "prevalence_b2_anemia_el_control",
                        "sd_b2_anemia_el_control")
df <- left_join(ineq, df_sqlns, by = "study") 
df <- left_join(df, df_control, by = "study")
df <- left_join(df, overall_prevalence_anemia, by = "study")

tau.method <- "REML" 
options(scipen = 999)
### RII control
meta1 <- metagen(TE = log(df$RII_control), lower = log(df$RII_low_control), upper =  log(df$RII_up_control), method.tau = tau.method, hakn = F, func.backtransf = exp,
                 studlab = df$study, prediction = TRUE)
